  "prompt": "What are some good young hard rock artist similar to bands like Rage Against The Machine, Wakrat, Foo Fighters, Downset, ACDC and Xombie etc?",
  "response": "Okay, finding bands that directly replicate the sound of Rage Against the Machine or AC/DC is tough because those bands are so iconic and unique. However, I can suggest some young hard rock artists that share elements of those bands' sounds, energy, and attitude. I'll break it down by which aspect they emulate.\n\n**For Rage Against the Machine-esque Rage & Political Fury:**\n\n*   **Nova Twins:** This UK duo is a force of nature. They blend heavy riffs with punk energy, electronic elements, and socially conscious lyrics. They have a powerful stage presence and a real message.\n*   **Bob Vylan:** Another UK band, this duo mixes punk, grime, and hardcore with scathing political commentary. Raw, aggressive, and confrontational, much like early RATM.\n*    **Static Dress:** A chaotic blend of metalcore, post-hardcore, and nu-metal with politically charged lyrics. Their live shows are known for their high energy.\n\n**For the Energetic Hard Rock of Foo Fighters:**\n\n*   **Cleopatrick:** This Canadian duo delivers raw, riff-driven hard rock with catchy hooks and a bluesy edge. Think early Royal Blood meets Queens of the Stone Age with a touch of Foo Fighters' accessibility.\n*   **Bad Nerves:** A British band playing high-energy power pop with punk and hard rock elements. Infectious melodies and driving rhythms make them a fun listen.\n\n**For the Groove and Heavy Riffs of Downset:**\n\n*   **Tetrarch:** This band delivers a potent mix of nu-metal, groove metal, and djent. Heavy riffs, aggressive vocals, and a dark atmosphere.\n*   **Vended:** With the son of Corey Taylor from Slipknot on vocals, this band mixes nu-metal, hardcore, and metalcore. High energy and aggression.\n\n**For the Raw Power and Simplicity of AC/DC:**\n\n*   **Airbourne:** This Australian band is the closest modern equivalent to AC/DC you'll find. They wear their influences on their sleeves and deliver pure, unadulterated hard rock.\n\n**For Xombie Type Heavy Hardcore/Metalcore:**\n\n*   **Vein.fm:**  Known for their chaotic and experimental metalcore sound, blending elements of nu-metal, hardcore, and industrial music.  Aggressive and intense.\n*   **Code Orange:** This band blurs the lines between hardcore, metalcore, and industrial music, creating a brutal and unsettling sound. They're known for their intense live shows.\n\n**Key Considerations:**\n\n*   **\"Young\" is Relative:** Some of these bands have been around for a few years, but they're still relatively new to the mainstream compared to the bands you listed.\n*   **Genre Blending:** Many modern bands blend genres, so you might find elements of different styles in their music.\n*   **Explore Further:** Use these recommendations as a starting point. Look at related artists and bands that these groups have toured with to discover even more new music.\n\nI encourage you to check out these bands on YouTube, Spotify, or Apple Music to see which ones resonate with you. Have fun exploring!",
